    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A type of Numidian marble that is white or yellow with purplish veins; it resembles pavonazetto marble which has led scholars to believe the name is a corruption of 'pavonazetta.'</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Tipo de mármol númida blanco o amarillo con venas violetas. Se asemeja al mármol pavonazetto, lo que ha hecho que muchos estudiosos crean que el nombre es una corrupción de "pavonazetta."
</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Type Numidisch marmer dat wit of geel is met purperachtige aderen. Het lijkt op pavonazzettomarmer, waardoor wetenschappers denken dat de naam een verbastering is van 'pavonazetta'.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052480/Jongste, Marmer in de Romeinse samenleving (1995)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>一種努米底亞大理石，呈白色或黃色，帶紫色脈紋，外觀與孔雀大理石（pavonazetto marble）相似，故有學者認為「paonazzo」一名有可能為「pavonazetto」一詞誤傳混用而來。 </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
